# t/mail/inbound-real.test — real inbound MIME through the parser + router (docs/13).
#
# A genuine Fastmail message — multipart/alternative, an RFC-2047 base64 encoded
# subject, real Return-Path/Received/DKIM/X-Spam headers — captured from the live
# kasi@decode.ee inbox and delivered byte-for-byte with `deliver { raw }`. The
# best parser test cases are the ones reality wrote: this proves käsi parses and
# routes real-world bytes, in any ring (deliver -raw is ring-agnostic).

send allow-sender { address support@fastmail.com }

deliver { raw t/cassettes/mail/inbound/welcome.eml }

task 1 route is main
task 1 status is awaiting-agent
task 1 participants are support@fastmail.com
